/*
CSS for Hanamikoji on BGA

Main features are reduced whitespace/margins and a fixed spot for waiting_card_zone. (cf. https://boardgamearena.com/bug?id=86954 & https://boardgamearena.com/bug?id=86955)

It should work fine on windows/screens 1280px or wider and with "Player area position" set to "Above". Some margins are pretty tight. So in some edge cases cards overlap other graphics slightly (e.g. 5*5).

test-game: https://boardgamearena.com/archive/replay/230419-1000/?table=369789824&player=1259869&comments=1259869;
(choose 1 out of 3 as 1st play from opponent)
*/

#waiting_card_zone {
    position: absolute;
    display: inline;
}

/* #mycard_wrap_playerID */
#this_player_block > div:nth-of-type(2) {
    display: flex;
    margin: auto auto auto 260px;
}

#mynothand_wrap, #myreserved_wrap, #mydiscarded_wrap {
    width: fit-content;
}

#myhand_wrap, #mynothand_wrap {
    margin: 5px 15px;
}

.geisha_card_wrap {
  height: 145px;
  margin: 5px auto;
}

/* #card_wrap_playerID */
#opponent_block > div:nth-of-type(1) {
   margin: -15px 10px auto auto;
}

/* #action_wrap_playerID */
#opponent_block > div:nth-of-type(2)  {
    margin: 5px auto auto 10px;
}
